## Rule File Structure

### Location
- All rules MUST be in `.cursor/rules/` directory
- Rules are `.mdc` files (Markdown with frontmatter)
- Rules are organized by category in subdirectories

### Reading Rules
- ✅ Use `read_file` tool to read rule files
- ✅ Use `list_dir` to see available rules
- ✅ Use `grep` to search rule content
- ❌ Never rely on cached rule content

### Updating Rules
- ✅ Use `search_replace` for partial updates
- ✅ Use `write` for complete rewrites
- ✅ Always verify changes with `read_file` after updating
- ❌ Never assume changes are saved without verification

